  "teacher_notes": {
    "objective": "Students will be able to identify, count, and write numbers 1-20 in English and Spanish. They will also be able to match number words to numerals and quantities.",
    "suggested_use": "Introduce numbers 1-10 first, then 11-20. Use flashcards for whole group and small group practice. The mini-book can be read aloud, then students can color and take home. Worksheets can be used for independent practice or in learning centers. Incorporate songs and counting games.",
    "materials_needed": [
      "Flashcards (number words, numerals, and quantities 1-20)",
      "Crayons, markers, or colored pencils",
      "Manipulatives (e.g., counting bears, unifix cubes, blocks)",
      "Number line (1-20)",
      "Scissors (for mini-book assembly)"
    ],
    "differentiation_tips": [
      "**Support:** Provide physical manipulatives for counting. Focus on numbers 1-10 before moving to 11-20. Offer hand-over-hand guidance for tracing. Use a number line as a visual aid. Allow students to point to numbers rather than always saying them.",
      "**Challenge:** Ask students to write sentences using numbers (e.g., 'I see seven birds.'). Introduce simple addition or subtraction problems using numbers 1-5. Encourage skip counting by 2s or 5s. Have students create their own number stories."
    ]
  },
